# NOTE: verify.html is intentionally NOT ignored — it MUST be committed and pushed
# so GitHub Pages can serve the public verification page.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# AUTHORING TOOLS — not needed by the live site (GitHub Pages
# only serves the generated HTML + the data/ JSON it fetches).
# These stay on your machine so you can still rebuild pages,
# but they don't clutter the public repo.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Build scripts (you run these locally to regenerate pages)
build-modules.py
build-recordings.py

# Per-folder source configs (read only by the build scripts;
# the generated index.html already has everything baked in)
self-paced/module-*/config.json
videos/week-*/config.json

# Page templates used by the build scripts
self-paced/_module_template.html
self-paced/_coming_soon_template.html

# NOTE: data/jokes.json and data/flashcards.json are NOT ignored —
# the live jokes & flashcards pages fetch them at runtime. Keep them.

